🌹📿My parents’ yard has been growing the most INSANE smelling roses. So I made rose petal beads lol. We noticed that the “clay” leaves a beautiful stain, so I used some freshly shaped beads as stamps to stain some white cloth :)

Rose petal beads have been made for centuries. When worn, body heat gently releases the scent from the rose oil. Somehow, they’ll keep their smell for years. 

Rose petal bead steps 

Collect 8-12 roses

De-petal

Add petals and water in blender (or mash with mortar and pestle) using 1/4 cup water per 2 cups petals

Blend well

Pour mixture into pot (different types might provide slightly different results)

Use or make double boiler, and stir constantly until clay like constancy (at least a few hours)
Remove from heat, let cool until handle-able temperature 

Shape beads and carefully poke holes (keep in mind that the beads will shrink to half their size)

Let beads sit in the sun for a few days (bringing them inside at night) until hardened and fully dry
